# Feature-Sliced Design (FSD)

Structure all source code under `src/` using FSD layers, ordered from highest to lowest level of abstraction:

```
src/
  app/        # App-wide setup: providers, global styles, routing root
  pages/      # Full page compositions
  widgets/    # Self-contained UI blocks composed from features/entities
  features/   # User-facing interactions (e.g. auth-by-email, add-to-cart)
  entities/   # Business domain objects (e.g. user, product, order)
  shared/     # Reusable low-level code with no business logic
    ui/        # Generic UI components (maps to current src/components/ui/)
    lib/       # Utilities (maps to current src/lib/)
    api/       # Base API client / request helpers
    config/    # Env vars, constants
```

## Rules

- **Imports only go downward**: a layer may only import from layers below it.
  - `pages` → `widgets` → `features` → `entities` → `shared`
  - Never import upward (e.g. `shared` must not import from `features`)
- Each layer (except `app` and `shared`) is divided into **slices** (domain concepts).
- Each slice exposes a single **public API** via its `index.ts`; never import from internal paths.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
import { UserCard } from '~/entities/user'

// ❌ BAD — bypasses public API
import { UserCard } from '~/entities/user/ui/UserCard'
```

- Slices contain **segments**: `ui/`, `model/`, `api/`, `lib/`, `config/`
